
<sect2><title>Under Windows</title>

<para>
The videolan client  works under Windows 95/98.ME/2000/XP. You can download a Windows
Installer or a Zip file from the <ulink url="http://www.videolan.org/vlc/download.html">vlc download page</ulink>. Execute he Windows installer or unzip the file in a directory to install vlc.
</para>

</sect2>

<sect2><title>Under BeOS</title>

<para>
You can download a Zip file from the <ulink
url="http://www.videolan.org/vlc/download.html">vlc download
page</ulink>. Unzip the file in a directory to install videolan client
</para>

</sect2>

<sect2><title>Under Mac OS X</title>

<para>
Download the Mac OS X pachage from the <ulink
url="http://www.videolan.org/vlc/download.html">vlcdowload page</ulink> and double-click on the icon of the package.
</para>

</sect2>

<sect2><title>under Linux Debian</title>

<para>
Edit as root /etc/apt/sources.list and add the following lines :
</para>

<para>
<screen><userinput>
	deb http://www.videolan.org/pub/videolan/debian $(ARCH)/
	deb-src http://www.videoaln.org/pub/videolan/debian sources/
</userinput></screen>
</para>

<para>
Then type as root :
</para>

<para>
<screen><userinput>
	#apt-get update
	#apt-get install vlc-gnome vlc-mad libdvdcss2
</userinput></screen>
</para>

</sect2>

<sect2><title>Under Linux Redhat, Mandrake and SuSE</title>

<para>
Install liba52 and libmad0. They should be packaged in your distribution. If they are not, try to find the RPMs on the Internet.
</para>

<para>
Download the RPM package of libdvdcss from <ulink url="http://www.videolan.org/libdvdcss/download.html">libdvdcss vlc</ulink>.
</para>

<para>
Donwload the RPm package of libdvdpsi from <ulink url="http://www.videolan.org/libdvbpsi/download.html">libdvdpsi download page</ulink>.
</para>

<para>
Download the RPM packages vlc vlc-gnome and vlc-mad from the <ulink url="http://www.videolan.org/vlc/download.html">vlc download page</ulink>.
</para>

<para>
To install the RPM packages : As root, type: 
</para>

<para>
<screen><userinput>
	# rpm -Uhv vlc-versionmdk.i586.rmp vlc-mad-versionmdk.i586.rpm vlc-gnome-versionmdk.i586.rpm 
        libdvdcss2-version.i586.rpm libdvdpsi1-version.i586.rpm
</userinput></screen>
</para>

</sect2>

<sect2><title>Under Unix and Linux</title>

<para>The method below is for any Unix or Linux supported by the
videolan client. We are going to compile and install the libraries and then the vlc.
</para>

<sect3><title>Install the libraries</title>

<para>
Many librairies are needed for particular uses:
</para>

<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>libdvdcss if you want to read encrypted DVDs</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>libdvdpsi if you want to read from network. (not compulsory for
them ofr the moment),</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>a52dec if you want to decode AC3</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>ffmpeg and libmadif if you want to read MPEG 4/DivX files.</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>

<para>Download the librairies from the VideoLAn FTP site, <ulink url="ftp://ftp.videolan.org/pub/videolan/vlc"></ulink>, in the directory version/contrib.
</para>

<para> For each librarie, uncompress, configure, compile and install :
</para>

<para>
<screen>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> tar -xvzf librairies.tar.gz</userinput>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> cd librairie</userinput>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> ./configure</userinput>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> make</userinput>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> su</userinput>
	<userinput> [enter root password]</userinput>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> make install
</userinput></screen>
</para>

<para>
Check that the configuration file /etc/ld.so.conf contains the line:
</para>

<para>
<screen><userinput>
	/usr/local/lib
</userinput></screen>
</para>

</sect3>

<sect3><title>Install vlc</title>

<para>
Download the sources of the lastest release : get the file
vlc-version.tar.gz from the <ulink url="http://www.videolan.org/vlc/download.html">vlc download page</ulink>. Uncompress : 
</para>

<para>
<screen>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> tar xvzf vlc-version.tar.gz</userinput>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> cd vlc-version
</userinput></screen>
</para>

<para>For the vlc 0.5.0 version type:</para>

<para>
<screen>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> ./bootstrap</userinput>
</screen>
</para>

<para>To get the list of configuration options, do :</para>

<para>
<screen>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> ./configure --help </userinput>
</screen>
</para>

<para>
Configure the videolan client. For example : 
</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>If you want  basic vlc, do : </para> <para><screen>	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput>./configure</userinput></screen></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>If you want the Gnome interface instead of the GTK interface (you
will need the developpemnt packages of Gnome)</para><para>
<screen>	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> ./configure --enable-gnome</userinput></screen></para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>If you want a full lvc with libdvbpsi, ffmpeg and mad (a52 and
libdvdcss are enabled by default:</para>
<para>
<screen>	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> ./configure --enable-dvbpsi --enable-mad --enable-ffmpeg --with-ffmpeg-tree=/usr/local/src/ffmpeg-date</userinput></screen></para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>

<para>
If you uncompressed ffmpeg in the directory /usr/local/src/ffmpeg-date.
</para>

<para>
To compile and install the vlc 0.5.0 you must use the automake 1.5 or
higher version. The automake 1.6 is highly recommanded.
</para>

<para>
Then, compile and install:
</para>

<para>
<screen>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> make</userinput>
	<prompt>%</prompt><userinput> su</userinput>
	 [enter root password]
	<userinput># make install
</userinput></screen>
</para>

<para>
You can also do a make uninstall, make clean or make distclean as needed.
</para>

</sect3>
</sect2>
